> Uh, could you answer a quick question for me?  Does PKP hold the patent for
> its implementation of the RSA algorithm _or_ the algorithm itself?

My understanding is the patent is for: using RSA for secure communications,
(or part thereof).  The 'implementation' is not relevant, and the maths is
not patentable by itself.

I stand to be corrected by anyone who knows better.  :-)

